Attention Juniors and Seniors and their Parents/Guardians:
*All seniors will be taking the ACT for free at school on Sept. 22nd but in addition to that I wanted to share the information below provided by WNCC.

Below are ACT test dates that will be offered at the WNCC Harms Center in Scottsbluff and the dates highlighted in yellow will also be available at WNCC-Sidney campus.
Due to COVID-19 social distancing restrictions, registrations for Fall 2020 are limited! All students must wear a face covering, answer a short health survey and have their temperature checked before being admitted to test. All dates are subject to change in regards to Directed Health Measures or inclement weather. Have your students refer to the WNCC homepage for any closures before coming to test.

Students register at actstudent.org

Test Dates:

October 10, 2020
October 24, 2020
December 12, 2020
February 6, 2021
April 17, 2021
June 12, 2021
July 17, 2021

post_text:
We are excited to announce that the USDA has approved FREE meals to ALL kids through Dec. 31,2020. What this means for families is that your kids can get free breakfast/lunch at school regardless of income. If your child has money in their account they can use that to purchase extras or it will remain there for use when we start charging again. As people return to work and our schools reopen it remains critical that our children continue to receive a healthy nutritious meal during this tough time. If anything changes in the near future we will be sure to update you.

https://docs.google.com/document/d/1S4EJ8RLg03zUg88qlq6nqHy6siwnwm4kAkTogpOKzmM/edit?usp=drivesdk

Sidney Public Schools has started a new career pathways internship for students at Sidney High School. This internship is partnering with our RaiderMade business classes to produce student/staff portraits for the 2020-2021 school year. This opportunity will teach our students about photography, business, marketing, as well as customer service. In addition, our student interns will learn how to photograph activities and sports.

Check out our website using the link below:

Sidney High School:

For Monday start of school. Important items.
Students will be allowed to carry backpacks throughout the day as well as use their locker.
Students and staff must wear masks if they are unable to physically distance or while they are on the move in hallways between classes.
Juniors and seniors will have the privilege of open campus for lunch. Students who remain on campus will eat lunch in the commons or in the gym. Juniors and seniors can also eat outside at the picnic tables that are located outside each locker room.
Mr. Arent will send out more details on Saturday about Monday's opening.

This was a difficult decision to make and involved hours of discussion, however, Cool Kids Club will be offering care for Kindergarten- 4th Grade. With the current guidelines from the Department of Health and Human Services and Panhandle Public Health District and Unified Command, we simply cannot offer care for 5th and 6th grade students at this time. This could change as this is an evolving situation. If something changes, we will notify the community as soon as possible. We offer our sincerest apologies, but this is the hand we have been dealt and we will continue to offer the best care at the most affordable pricing.

Kim Hofrock
CKC Sidney Public School After School Program Director

post_text: Wishing you all the best this upcoming season! Congratulations to you all!
shared_text:
Michelle Weimer is with Amy Neumann.
July 24 at 6:36 AM ·

Words can’t even express how proud I am my dance team this year!!! They have practiced so hard on zoom and taken virtual learning by storm! Not only have they been able to learn routines through zoom they have been able to create some team bonding memories to last a lifetime. They were able to successfully perform and earn a superior rating for their home and team performances at our home camp this week! In 3 short days they learned a total of 8 routines and every single team member earned a blue ribbon for their performances of those routines! We had 8 All American nominees and truly made it impossible for instructors to pick just 4 of them for the All American team as they had tears that they could not pick all 8 as they thought all 8 deserved the honor! The sky is the limit and I cannot wait to see what this team can accomplish in such an uncertain time in the world

"twenty-twenty has been a year of unexpected challenges, but we are here today to celebrate overcoming them. As we pursue our future endeavours we must always remember to face the challenges head on, we must persist despite failures, and we must seek the challenges that lie ahead. I mentioned some of the hardships we all have faced this year. I hope, however, we will not be defined by these hardships, but will be known as the class determined to succeed regardless of the circumstances.

Thank you, and congratulations to the class of 2020."

Benjamin Bashtovoi
Valedictorian
Sidney High School, Class of 2020

Attention Parents/Guardians:

The first day of school for Sidney Public School students will be August 17th and not August 13th, as originally published. The reason for this change is to give our staff more time to prepare for the opening of school under the new guidelines that have been developed due to COVID-19. The start of school plan will be made public before August 1st. This has not been made public yet as we are continuing to update as directives change.

Thank you for your patience regarding the ongoing challenges we continue to face as a result of the Covid-19 Pandemic.

Jay Ehler
Superintendent
Sidney Public Schools

LIBRARY BOOK RETURN DAY FOR NORTH, SOUTH and CENTRAL ELEMENTARY is at the SOUTH BUILDING ON FRIDAY!

North, South and Central families can return library books on Friday, April 24th from 8am-2pm. SOUTH ELEMENTARY is the only drop-off location on Friday.
A tote will be placed outside the front doors at South. Please put any SPS library books you'd like to return in the tote. We will have other days to return books in the future. You are welcome to keep books at home until the next return day in May. Please message Mrs. Ramsey directly on Class DoJo or email jennifer.ramsey@raidermail.org if you have any questions about the book(s) checked out to your student. Thank you!

Sidney Raiders added a new photo — with Heidi Marker Ahrens and 2 others at Sidney High School (Nebraska).
April 21 at 8:54 AM · Sidney, NE ·

Sidney High School, Class of 2020 Senior Showcase - Elijah Ahrens. Eli is the son of Joel and Heidi Ahrens. He plans to attend Concordia University on a football scholarship.

“In the past few years I have gained an amazing crew of friends. I miss seeing them everyday, laughing and making memories in school, to wrap up our Senior year. Who would have ever thought that it could be gone in a blink of an eye. So much that we took for granted, I would give anything just to walk those halls of Sidney High School one more time to live it like it was my last day to see my friends one more time and the Sidney Staff as well. I am thankful that we have had such and amazing staff and Community that support our school and students. When the quarantine is over, I can't wait to spend time with my friends until we all have to go our separate ways."

We wish you all the best of luck Eli!
#NSAASeniorSalute

Starting Monday April 20th, please return any books checked out from the MS/HS Media Center to the tote just inside the first set of doors, on the east side of the high school. This goes for both Middle School and High School students.

If you think a book was returned, or not checked out to you, please email Mr. Gallaway, so he can check: roger.gallaway@raidermail.org.

But please be aware, if it is showing as checked out to you - you are ultimately responsible for it. Also, please check out the SORA app on your chromebooks for any ebooks that are available you might be interested in!

If you have books in your locker, just let Mr. Gallaway know, and he'll retrieve them for you.

Thanks,

Mr. Gallaway

Get EXCITED South Elementary Families

We are about 1 hour away from the 1st YouTube Live PC Mission hosted by your very own, Mr. Meyer! Here is a link to the YouTube Live video feed: https://youtu.be/Tt1AfqPb0iQ. If you subscribe to me, you can set it up to get notification when I do go live or post new videos.

Here is a link to the Flipgrid where you can post your video after your child has completed the challenge: https://flipgrid.com/c404902b. This is totally optional, you can just send me a picture/ video if you'd rather. But I thought this would be a great way to teach kids about sharing online and also give them a chance to see other kids work too! The password to get into this FlipGrid is South20!.

Here is a link to the supply list as well: https://docs.google.com/document/d/127u7TQqPJp1bvaUu7-skbkzNrIl9tKTgEnRzbLjNPyM/edit?usp=sharing.

Hopefully you can join, if not you can watch the video anytime after I have gone live and still participate!

post_text: The Sidney Public school nurses are so excited to be getting dress down funds for their new vision spot screener they have dressed up! The new vision screener will take 5 seconds or less to accurately test for numerous vision abnormalities. This will be especially valuable for the younger grades and preschoolers. Thank you Cheyenne County Chamber of Commerce for your dress down day funds on April 17th to help pay for our new screener. #thepowerofus

Tonight, Thursday at 6 PM, I will be having our very first PC Mission during our Learn from Home time. PC stands for Parent-Child and it is completely optional and tons of potential fun! I will be having a YouTube Live video starting at 6, it will only take around 15-20 minutes, so feel free to join if you can, if you can't you can still see the video at your leisure. post_text: Reminder - Kindergarten Registration Information
shared_text:
SCRIPT.GOOGLE.COM
Kindergarten Document Uploads

Sidney Raiders
April 8 at 2:48 PM ·

Reminder to parents of students who will be starting kindergarten in the fall of 2020 at Sidney Public Schools ... registration is open on our website www.sidneyraiders.org (you will see a link to register for kindergarten) on that page, you will find a link to upload documents. Uploading your student's birth certificate and/or immunizations now will save you time in the fall. Simply take a photo on your phone and upload it today. The files go directly into a folder that is only seen by SPS employees that need to see the information. Please take the time to fill out our registration and health information when you can and don't forget the ability to upload documents directly to us is an additional time saver. I am including a link to upload the documents below and if you still need to register, please visit our school website - www.sidneyraiders.org

Thank you!!

Sidney Red Raider Cross Country added 30 new photos to the album: Cross Country ... Through the Years.
April 10 at 3:07 PM ·

Hey Raiders ... let's have a little fun. This album is for all of our XC memories through the years. Submit any photo to add to our collection. Please just submit a caption to go along with it to explain the photo. Anyone can submit, just message it to Coach Wiedeburg on here or via text or Email and I will get it added. The more we get, the more fun this will be to look through. Maybe your favorite memory was last season or maybe it was your last season many years ago, maybe you went to Sidney or maybe you now coach for Sidney ... we will take them all!

May I introduce to you Sidney Middle School National Junior Honor Society Treasurer for the 2020-2021 school year - Kayla Westby.

"Hi, I’m Kayla Westby and I’m a 7th grader. Harold Kushner once said, “When you are kind to others, it not only changes you, it changes the world.” I feel character is the most important quality in NJHS. A person of character is respectful, honest, has the ability to be kind, and the desire to help others. These are all very important essentials in life. " - Kayla Westby, Class of 2025

Kayla is the daughter of Steve Westby and Kilee Rapp.

post_text: The Covid-19 pandemic is affecting every single one of us The well-being, health, and safety of people remains our top priority. We are doing everything we can to keep our employees and communities safe while we continue to support our children and do our part to help combat this pandemic. At this time we have decided to move our lunch/breakfast pick up to two days a week in order to limit contact. Pick up will now be on Tuesday and Thursday only. Starting NEXT WEEK families will get multiple days of lunch/breakfast in order to ensure a week's worth of meals. Thank you for your understanding at this time. #RaiderStrong

post_text:
1st of 4 showcases for Sidney High School, Class of 2020, 12 Sport Athletes, featuring Kendra Nesbitt.

"Being a 12 sport athlete has taught me to be a better person, a stronger leader and a more confident role model. Sports has taught me time management and that education extends beyond the classroom. The support I’ve received in the past four years from teammates and Sidney High School is incredible! Being a 12 sport athlete has given me the opportunity to make countless memories and experiences that I can draw from over and over in life. Being able to be a 12 sport athlete has been a blessing and I would not trade the past 4 years for anything!

The one quote I have lived by since I can remember, is something my mom has always told me, "It's not what you did or said, it's how you did it or said it." I did it with pride and I did it with all my heart."

Kendra Nesbitt
Sidney High School, Class of 2020
12 Sport Senior
Volleyball * Girls Basketball * Track

post_text:
This is Gus trying to understand nursing budgets.... The nurses at Sidney Public schools are also adjusting to a work at home environment.

We have learned how to use Zoom and Hangouts for virtual meeting and do this on a weekly basis to collaborate and unify our nursing duties.

Some of the things we work on from home are the following:
Professional development
On line registration for in coming kindergarteners.
Listening to Power of Positive Summit.
Finding Tdap dates immunizations for incoming 7th graders on the Nebraska Immunization site.
Working on our 2020/2021 budgets.
Update and look at nursing school policies and health programs at our schools.

We miss everyone and can’t wait to be back in action taking care of our students at school.
#RaiderStrong

Ashley Olivas Unk is with Shayla Schilz.
March 31 at 7:55 AM ·

*NEW LOPER SPOTLIGHT*

Shayla attends Sidney High School in Sidney, Nebraska, where she performs on the Dance Team. She plans to obtain her Nursing degree and become a Labor & Delivery Nurse, because she is passionate about helping others and she loves babies. Her interests include dancing, cruising, listening to all kinds of music, spending time with friends, enjoying nature, shopping, experiencing new things, and completing interior design projects. Shayla would love to travel in the future and get to know other parts of the world.

Shayla says, “I hope to branch out and meet new people throughout these next few years!”. We look forward to seeing you on campus in the fall, Shayla. Thank you for choosing the University of Nebraska at Kearney!

#BeBlueGoldBold #GoLopers

Shayla says, “I hope to branch out and meet new people throughout these next few years!”. We look forward to seeing you on campus in the fall, Shayla. Thank you for choosing the University of Nebraska at Kearney!

#BeBlueGoldBold #GoLopers

The hallways are quiet but the RaiderNation is very much NOT quiet. Our students aren’t visible but our spirit is very much visible! We have a book mobile running around town to deliver books, to our food service personnel, who are working hard to feed our community kids, to a staff parade coming up next week, our 7th grade girls made an awesome video, SHS student council members are reading books on YouTube and teachers are live streaming into students homes. Keep sending in your #RaiderStrong clips and we will keep sharing our spirit.
#raidernationdays2020

Sidney Singers Seinn O April 10, 2018

David F. Mead
March 25 at 5:48 AM ·

I miss making music with my choirs. But here’s the thing. Many music teachers become teachers because of what they believe they can do for the world of music. I became a music teacher because of what music has done for me. I want my choirs to know that music is a gift from God, it isn’t about me. It’s all about the music, and music is enough!
